CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1952, pg. 27, reads: "Ready for Comeback - Bob Baker, center, signs a contract for his coming fight here Oct. 28. The bout will be Baker's first in almost a year.  The promising battler has been sidelined with injured hands.  Others in photo are standing left, to right, T. W. Stephens, Wilkinsburg burgess; Promoter Anthony (Cowboy) DeLuca.  Seated next to Baker is his manager, William Better. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Boxer Bob Baker signing contract, surrounded by T. W. Stephen, Anthony "Cowboy" DeLuca, William Bettor, and another man, in office
